<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,258,1798]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1735,1761]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[848,911,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">erexit</emphasis>
”—raised, and refers to the characteristic patch of raised scales on the forewing.
</paragraph>
